The paper focuses on enabling robots to learn cost functions from user guidance, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of online function approximation and different function spaces for the approximation suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The user study and subjective perceptions of the robot suggest a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the goal of enabling robots to learn from user guidance suggests a potential application in control systems (cs.SY).
